•Prof. Nnenna Oti The Governing Council of the Federal University of Technology, Owerri (FUTO) has appointed Prof Nnenna Oti as a new Vice Chancellor to succeed the outgoing vice chancellor, Prof. Francis Eze. The new vice chancellor Prof. Oti until her new appointment was the Deputy Vice Chancellor, AcademicHe emerged tops with  75.5 points to beat six other candidates. Her closest rival was Prof. Ikechukwu Dozie who scored 69.7 points. Pro-Chancellor and Chairman of Council, Prof. John Offem announced the appointment of the new vice chancellor by 9.30pm after a day-long selection and interview of the seven candidates that scaled through the initial selection process. Prof. Offem said that there were a total of 29 applications at the initial stage and only seven emerged after final selection. Prof Oti hails from Ebonyi State. By Hilary Akalugwu Nsukka (Enugu State ) - Prof. Charles Igwe has emerged as the new Vice-Chancellor of the University of Nigeria Nsukka (UNN). Chief Okwun Omeaku, the Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the university disclosed this to the News Agency (NAN) in a telephone interview in Nsukka on Thursday.… In "Top Stories" By George Odok Calabar  - Some members of the National Assembly from Cross River have congratulated Prof. Florence Banku-Obi on her emergence as the first female Vice Chancellor elect of the University of Calabar. Their congratulatory letters were made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Monday in… In "Education" … He had barely settled into office as VC when we began to notice lack of transparency under his management - Council Despite claims by Prof Oluwatoyin Ogundipe that he was not given fear hearing on allegations of financial malpractices before he was sacked as the Vice Chancellor of the… In "News"